wikipedia_page.main: Joseph Rathborne (11 May 1807, Lincoln, England – 12 August 1842, Cowes) was an English Roman Catholic priest and controversialist.

response: Doyle was a good friend of John Henry Newman, and wrote to him in 1841 expressing the regrets of Southwark Catholic clergy for the attack on the Tractarians made by Joseph Rathborne. Doyle published frequently in The Tablet, as "Father Thomas". He died at St George's Cathedral on 6 June 1879, and was buried there.
